"{\"uid\": \"salon.com-2024-09-17-jordan-chiles-appeals-unfair-olympics-bronze-medal-decision\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Team USA gymnast Jordan Chiles is still fighting to get herbronze medalback.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 76, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 8, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9990177712148522, \"rank\": 0.0006394923297818919, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 17, \"end\": 30, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordan Chiles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympian filed an appeal of the decision that saw the Court of Arbitration for Sport (CAS) force her to cede her third-place title in the floor event to Ana B\\u00c4\\u0083rbosu of Romania, per an announcement made by her attorneys on Monday.\\u00c2  Chiles is now appealing the decision in Switzerland, where CAS is headquartered.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cFrom start to finish, the procedures leading to the CAS panel\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s decision were fundamentally unfair, and it is no surprise that they resulted in an unjust decision,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d the athlete's lawyers said in a statement,per CNN.\\u00c2\\u00a0\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cChiles believes in competing fairly and with integrity and holding these organizations to the standards and rules that were established to ensure fairness,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Chiles' legal team continued.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cJordan Chiles\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 appeals present the international community with an easy legal question\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094will everyone stand by while an Olympic athlete who has done only the right thing is stripped of her medal because of fundamental unfairness in an ad-hoc arbitration process?\", \"from\": 78, \"to\": 1090, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 82, \"end\": 87, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999996779852791, \"rank\": 3.220157602436451e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 88, \"end\": 96, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999925223619, \"rank\": 7.477643467148073e-09, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 257, \"end\": 264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"score\": 0.9988440159596347, \"rank\": 0.0010081640979546364, \"text\": \"Romania\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\"}, {\"begin\": 361, \"end\": 372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9994378828194984, \"rank\": 0.0005602349687031698, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}, {\"begin\": 380, \"end\": 383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0952711162608306e-21, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 459, \"end\": 462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0952711162608306e-21, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The answer to that question should be no,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d said Chiles' lawyer, Maurice M. Suh.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cEvery part of the Olympics, including the arbitration process, should stand for fair play,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Suh added,\\\" Suh added.\", \"from\": 1091, \"to\": 1294, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1157, \"end\": 1164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maurice_Gibb\", \"score\": 0.9998457172132764, \"rank\": 0.00011811546754365646, \"text\": \"Maurice\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maurice_Gibb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maurice_Gibb\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The United States Olympic and Paralympic Committee (USOPC) had openly supported Chiles in her mission to see her medal reinstated.\\u00c2\\u00a0\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cDue to the egregious errors and oversight by CAS in handling the case and overlooking clear evidence of Jordan\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s rightful Bronze win, we are determined to ensure she receives the recognition she deserves.\", \"from\": 1296, \"to\": 1637, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1300, \"end\": 1313, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997884089848019, \"rank\": 0.00021138769286687173, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1476, \"end\": 1479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0952711162608306e-21, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Our commitment to truth in this matter remains steadfast,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d the USPOC told CNN.\\u00c2  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026 Salon.com, LLC